This paper deals with the generation of videos of complex scenes, specifically human-object interaction videos. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel adversarial framework for generating these videos, which involves multiple discriminators and focuses on different aspects of the video. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework on two challenging datasets, which indicates that it may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
